      "size": {
        "height": 51,
        "width": 340
      }
    },
    {
      "content": "The `flip-flop` node changes the state on the `MEM` pin from 0 to 1 every 30 seconds. Fortunately, the boolean and number data types are compatible with each other — `true` and `false` are automatically converted to `1` and `0` for the `map-range` `X` input\n",
      "id": "S14Ht0S9b",
      "position": {
        "x": 510,
        "y": 102
      },
      "size": {
        "height": 51,
        "width": 612
      }
    },
    {
      "content": "The `servo` node receives a value from 0 to 1 in the `VAL` pin, which corresponds to the rotation of the shaft from 0° to 180°, respectively.",
      "id": "SJ7uYCrqb",
      "position": {
        "x": 476,
